{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It wasn't like today, you go into a Waldbaum's, and you say, give me 3 pounds of whatever-- you know, matzahs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There, you-- you-- you worked for it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you appreciated it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And after-- all right, this was Passover, mostly Passover.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Also, Passover was the holiday where if somebody got a new suit or a new pair of shoes or whatever, it was for Passover.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was the time when-- when-- when the kids used to get new clothes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] During the High Holy Days-- Shovuos, for example.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "After Passover comes Shovuos.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now Shovuos is that holiday when-- when-- when Jews are reminded that they received the Torah.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In every house, they used to go out and tear off branches from walnut trees because the walnut tree is in bloom.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it has a very good smell.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they would put in the house full of branches with walnut trees.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This supposedly is to remind the Jews that they were-- were standing on Mount Sinai because it looked like a-- like a mountain there, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Rosh Hashanah-- even so we were a small village, we used to hire the best [HEBREW] the best [HEBREW] in the area because we appreciated a good chazzan.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, to this day, I am the [HEBREW] here in the Shelter Rock Jewish Center, which is a modern Orthodox-- I mean, a modern conservative congregation.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We have about 700 members in our congregation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I'm the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I still daven on the same nusach, on the same-- the way I remember it from my hometown.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it's surprising to know that many time, young people walk over to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they say, you know something, I really appreciate the way you-- the way you daven because it has a certain Jewish [HEBREW] to it which was squeezed out in America.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I don't know what happened to it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But it's-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Night.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I want you to know that our village didn't have no electricity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the first time they brought in electricity to my village was in the '80s, maybe about 15 years ago, for the first time that my village was electrified.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And so in shul, they used to-- every family would come with a huge candle, about 3 feet high.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And there was a table.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they would mount those candles on the table.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So when you walked into shul in Yom Kipper night, everything was dark-- [HEBREW] night, I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But you see about 26 candles in the main.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It gave it a certain flavor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It gave it a certain holiness, a certain awe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The woman, most of them, were dressed in white.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Everybody in the family was in shul.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Some of the man stayed in shul all night long until Yom Kippur was over.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was one time when I went to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Well, see, my village was a small village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "But a lot of people used to go to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And I remember once, me and my father, we went down to the Spinka Rebbe for Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "It was a big thing for the Hasidic-- I wouldn't say we were Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "But over there, everybody belonged to a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "This rebbe, by the way, was not only a rebbe, a teacher.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "He was also a miracle maker.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "If you had a problem in business, in business, you went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "You were sick, you went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I remember my father once-- it's just a thought which I have right now-- he went to the rebbe, you know, because he was a farmer.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And-- and-- and when he brought in things from the-- from the farm, was-- it was-- there was hardly anything-- anything-- you know, the-- it was a very poor harvest.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And my father was-- we had six children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he asked the rebbe what to do because he wouldn't have enough bread for the children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the rebbe told him to buy two sheep because he told him, from sheep, you get wool, you get milk, you could get meat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And sheep is going to be a blessing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he bought two sheeps.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He borrowed money.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He bought two sheep.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think about-- took about three, four months, and the two sheep died.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So could-- couldn't-- and my father was a very successful businessmen, as you could see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after that, he bought a goat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And to tell you the story about a goat, see, I think we'll need another interview for that.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
